Enumeration Type Documentation

enum pSDKParameter

Parameters enums to be used as the 1st arg to setParameter or getParameter.

See also:
PhysicManager.setParameter() PhysicManager.getParameter()
Enumerator:
pSDKP_SkinWidth 

Default value for pShape::skinWidth.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 0.025
Unit: distance.

See also:
pShape.setSkinWidth
pSDKP_DefaultSleepLinVelSquared 

The default linear velocity, squared, below which objects start going to sleep. Note: Only makes sense when the pSDKP_BF_ENERGY_SLEEP_TEST is not set.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: (0.15*0.15)

pSDKP_DefaultSleepAngVelSquared 

The default angular velocity, squared, below which objects start going to sleep. Note: Only makes sense when the pSDKP_BF_ENERGY_SLEEP_TEST is not set.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: (0.14*0.14)

pSDKP_BounceThreshold 

A contact with a relative velocity below this will not bounce.

Range: (-inf, 0]
Default: -2

See also:
pMaterial
pSDKP_DynFrictScaling 

This lets the user scale the magnitude of the dynamic friction applied to all objects.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 1

See also:
pMaterial
pSDKP_StaFrictionScaling 

This lets the user scale the magnitude of the static friction applied to all objects.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 1

See also:
pMaterial
pSDKP_MaxAngularVelocity 

See the comment for pRigidBody::setMaxAngularVelocity() for details.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 7

See also:
pRigidBody.setMaxAngularVelocity()
pSDKP_ContinuousCD 

Enable/disable continuous collision detection (0.0f to disable).

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 0.0

See also:
NxPhysicsSDK.createCCDSkeleton()
pSDKP_AdaptiveForce 

Used to enable adaptive forces to accelerate convergence of the solver.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 1.0

pSDKP_CollVetoJointed 

Controls default filtering for jointed bodies. True means collision is disabled.

Range: {true, false}
Default: true

See also:
pSDKP_JF_CollisionEnabled
pSDKP_TriggerTriggerCallback 

Controls whether two touching triggers generate a callback or not.

Range: {true, false}
Default: true

See also:
NxUserTriggerReport
pSDKP_CCDEpsilon 

Distance epsilon for the CCD algorithm.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 0.01

pSDKP_SolverConvergenceThreshold 

Used to accelerate solver.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 0

pSDKP_BBoxNoiseLevel 

Used to accelerate HW Broad Phase.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 0.001

pSDKP_ImplicitSweepCacheSize 

Used to set the sweep cache size.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 5.0

pSDKP_DefaultSleepEnergy 

The default sleep energy threshold. Objects with an energy below this threshold are allowed to go to sleep. Note: Only used when the pSDKP_BF_ENERGY_SLEEP_TEST flag is set.

Range: [0, inf)
Default: 0.005

pSDKP_ConstantFluidMaxPackets 

Constant for the maximum number of packets per fluid. Used to compute the fluid packet buffer size in NxFluidPacketData.

Range: [925, 925]
Default: 925

See also:
NxFluidPacketData
pSDKP_ConstantFluidMaxParticlesPerStep 

Constant for the maximum number of new fluid particles per frame. Range: [4096, 4096]
Default: 4096.

pSDKP_AsynchronousMeshCreation 

[Experimental] Disables scene locks when creating/releasing meshes.

Prevents the SDK from locking all scenes when creating and releasing triangle meshes, convex meshes, height field meshes, softbody meshes and cloth meshes, which is the default behavior. Can be used to improve parallelism but beware of possible side effects.

Warning:
Experimental feature.
pSDKP_ForceFieldCustomKernelEpsilon 

Epsilon for custom force field kernels.

This epsilon is used in custom force field kernels (NxSwTarget). Methods like recip() or recipSqrt() evaluate to zero if their input is smaller than this epsilon.


pSDKP_ImprovedSpringSolver 

Enable/disable improved spring solver for joints and wheelshapes.

This parameter allows to enable/disable an improved version of the spring solver for joints and wheelshapes.

Warning:
The parameter is introduced for legacy purposes only and will be removed in future versions (such that the improved spring solver will always be used).
Note:
Changing the parameter will only affect newly created scenes but not existing ones.

Range: {0: disabled, 1: enabled}
Default: 1

pSDKP_PARAMS_NUM_VALUES 

This is not a parameter, it just records the current number of parameters (as max(NxParameter)+1) for use in loops. When a new parameter is added this number should be assigned to it and then incremented.
